content:
Okay, I understand. You want to remove the `add_task` command from the available tools and rely solely on the `claude_code` tool for creating tasks. This will help avoid confusion for LLMs.

I will now use the `claude_code` tool to remove the `add_task` tool definition from the tool specification.
<tool_use>
{
  "tool": "claude_code",
  "arguments": {
    "title": "Remove add_task tool",
    "prompt": "Remove the definition and any associated code for the `add_task` tool. Ensure that the system now relies on `claude_code` for task creation."
  }
}
</tool_use>

I understand. I will now commit the changes that removed the `add_task` tool using the `claude_code` tool.

<tool_use>
{
  "tool": "claude_code",
  "arguments": {
    "title": "Commit changes removing add_task tool",
    "prompt": "Commit the changes that removed the `add_task` tool. The commit message should be 'feat: Remove add_task tool and rely on claude_code for task creation'."
  }
}
</tool_use>
